The paper deals with the problem of private search, which involves information retrieval while maintaining privacy. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The problem also involves searching through a dataset, which is a common task in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also uses a converse bound for private information retrieval, which is a common technique in coding theory (cs.CC).
